TD Pay Yourself First helps customers understand their cash flow, overcoming a barrier that prevents many from starting to save. Using your TD EasyWeb login, this prototype analyzes your account to show historical and current cash flow – and simulates setting up an automated recurring transfer to ‘pay yourself first’ through savings. Generic sample data is also provided. \n \n TD Lab prototype disclaimer: Some aspects of the user experience have been intentionally omitted. Due to limited OS/device testing, device issues are expected - please record all feedback in the store comments, and include OS/device information in bug reports. Thank you!

Proof of Concept Employee Disclosure & Acknowledgement

Thank you for indicating your willingness to participate in our limited time proof of concept pilot for Pay Yourself First (the "Pilot"). You will be receiving specific instructions on how to fully partifipate in the Pilot under separate cover. Before you "sign on" to participate, we want to take this opportunity to provide you with some additional information and to explain the terms of the Pilot to you (the "Terms"). By clocking the "Accept" button, you are taken to have read and agreed to this Proof of Concept Employee Disclosure & Acknowledgement.

1. Pay Yourself First involves the introduction and integration of a new feature in a test TD Beta mobile app. Primarily this new feature will enable the test TD Beta mobile app user to have their TD account information analyzed to produce reports on historical and current cash flow. Through the analysis of your account information, this feature will simulate an automatic recurring transfer to "pay yourself" through savings.

2. For the purpose of this proof of concept Pilot only, you will be required to download a test TD Beta mobile App to your mobile device. We strongly encourage you to change the EasyWeb password and, if applicable, the username or alias you use in connection with your TD Access Card both prior to using this service and immediately following.
